description:
&lt;p&gt;Directorate Pharmacist lead for the clinical directorates of Ear, Nose &amp; Throat; Head &amp; Neck; Maxillo-Facial; Dental; Ophthalmology plus Urology Directorates at Cardiff &amp; Vale University Health Board&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to the retirement of the existing post-holder we have an exciting opportunity for a motivated, enthusiastic and experienced clinical pharmacist to join our patient-focused and progressive Surgical Pharmacy Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have the opportunity to lead the pharmacy service for these six combined specialties within the Surgical Clinical Board and play an integral role in providing specialist pharmaceutical advice and support to these specialities both to inpatient and in outpatient clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our aim is to help and support you develop the clinical pharmacy services to these specialties as new pharmaceutical developments continue to be developed benefiting our patients. Our innovative services, backed by strong clinical support, are highly respected &amp; fully integrated within the Surgical Clinical Board. Your professionalism, excellent inter-personal skills &amp; enthusiasm will equip you to be a valued contributor to our service &amp; a key member of our supportive clinical pharmacy team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Cardiff and Vale UHB our values demonstrate our commitment to our patients:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• We care about the people we serve &amp; the people we work with&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• We trust &amp; respect one another&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• We take personal responsibility&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• We treat people with kindness&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• We act with integrity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cardiff’s cultural &amp; sporting facilities, the peace &amp; harmony of nearby National Parks, or the stimulating Welsh coastline, are matched by the many opportunity afforded its aspiring healthcare practitioners. Discover how you can enjoy life to the full &amp; progress your fulfilling career by sharing in our values, caring for people, keeping them well.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 11th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adrian Turk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Surgical Clinical Board Pharmacist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0290 746795&lt;/p&gt;
